<item>
            <title>[SUREFIRE-1857] JUnit 5 report does not contain assertion failure message</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-1857</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Since JUnit 5, if a test fails due to an assertion, the xml report does not contain the assertion message. According to the report specification, the message should be included:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&amp;lt;xs:element&#160;name=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;failure&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&#160;nillable=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&#160;minOccurs=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;0&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&#160;maxOccurs=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;unbounded&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;
    &amp;lt;xs:complexType&amp;gt;
        &amp;lt;xs:simpleContent&amp;gt;
            &amp;lt;xs:extension&#160;base=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;xs:string&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;
                &amp;lt;xs:attribute&#160;name=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;message&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&#160;type=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;xs:string&quot;&lt;/span&gt;/&amp;gt;
                &amp;lt;xs:attribute&#160;name=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;type&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&#160;type=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;xs:string&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&#160;use=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;required&quot;&lt;/span&gt;/&amp;gt;
            &amp;lt;/xs:extension&amp;gt;
        &amp;lt;/xs:simpleContent&amp;gt;
    &amp;lt;/xs:complexType&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;/xs:element&amp;gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Pom contains:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&amp;lt;build&amp;gt;
    &amp;lt;plugins&amp;gt;
        &amp;lt;plugin&amp;gt;
            &amp;lt;groupId&amp;gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&amp;lt;/groupId&amp;gt;
            &amp;lt;artifactId&amp;gt;maven-surefire-plugin&amp;lt;/artifactId&amp;gt;
            &amp;lt;version&amp;gt;3.0.0-M5&amp;lt;/version&amp;gt;
        &amp;lt;/plugin&amp;gt;
    &amp;lt;/plugins&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;/build&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Test:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;package&lt;/span&gt; com.example;

&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;

&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;MyTest {
    @Test
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; void test() {
        Assertions.assertEquals(1, 2, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;two is not one&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
    }
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Generated report:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&amp;lt;testcase name=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;test&quot;&lt;/span&gt; classname=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;com.example.MyTest&quot;&lt;/span&gt; time=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;0.018&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;
    &amp;lt;failure type=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;org.opentest4j.AssertionFailedError&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;![CDATA[org.opentest4j.AssertionFailedError: five is not six ==&amp;gt; expected: &amp;lt;5&amp;gt; but was: &amp;lt;6&amp;gt;
   at TestProject/com.example.MyTest.test(MyTest.java:9)
]]&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/failure&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;/testcase&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Possible reason for this behavior:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In version m3, RunListenerAdapter uses SimpleReportEntry.withException to generate the entry if the test failed due to an assertion&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since Version m4, a constructor of SimpleReportEntry is used, however it gets null as message&lt;/p&gt;</description>
